    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right that exemptions alone cannot erase the immediate financial burden on essential workers who have no viable alternative to driving. While the city's plan aims to provide relief, the reality is that many tradespeople and delivery drivers will still face significant costs that could force them to seek more expensive housing further out of the city or drop their deliveries. This highlights a critical flaw in the current proposal: without a massive, immediate investment in affordable housing and reliable last-mile public transit options, congestion pricing will disproportionately hurt the very workers it claims to protect.",
